title: Latest update is not an improvement
text:
Why do companies keep making their apps worse?  The updated look-and-feel is more spacious, which is nice ... except that I don't have space for a big, fat, mostly empty menu bar along the left edge.  Now there's less space for what actually matters, my contacts' names and the chats themselves, and they're all truncated or squashed.

Please shrink that menu bar, or give us the option to remove it altogether.  Facebook Messenger and Line have much thinner menu bars, and thus a more space-efficient interface.  iMessage has no menu bar at all.
